# Import the necessary libraries
import nltk
from nltk.sentiment.vader import SentimentIntensityAnalyzer
NLTK, or the Natural Language Toolkit, is a widely used library in the field of natural 
language processing (NLP) and text analysis. It's a comprehensive library that provides 
easy-to-use interfaces and 
resources for working with human language data. 

NLP 
nlp le natural human language lai computer program ma usable banaune ma focus garcha 

Tokenizing
split up text by word or by sentence
allow you to work with smaller pieces of text that are still relatively coherent and meaningful even outside of the context of the rest of the text. 
first step in turning unstructured data into structured data, that makes easy to analyze.

text lai analyze garda, tokenizing by words or tokenizing by sentence garincha 

Tokenizing by word:
Tokenizing your text by word allows you to identify words that come up particularly often
for eg valentine day ko post herda love vanne word frequently aucha 

Tokenizing by sentence:
you can analyze how those words relate to one another and see more context. 


Stemming

root word ma lancha
working cha vane work banaune

Tagging Parts of Speech

Part of speech is a grammatical term that deals with the roles words play when you use them together in sentences. Tagging parts of speech, or POS tagging, is the task of labeling the words in your text according to their part of speech.

noun pronoun adjective verb conjunction


Lemmatizing

stemming jastai ho, but it gives complete word
